{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17642750","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17642750"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T19:43:40+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T19:43:40+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17961"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17961","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17961"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.41,0.06,0.18,0.32,0.03]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10675"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76512"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10675","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10675"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17961"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62009"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"35"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4927"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"5789"},{"type":"tags","id":"5852"},{"type":"tags","id":"6746"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24863"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24865"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76512","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/76512"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 35-year-old woman presents to the General Practice clinic with a two-week history of nasal congestion, facial pain, and pressure around her eyes. She reports that the symptoms worsen when she leans forward. She has no significant medical history and does not take any regular medications. On examination, she appears well with vital signs within normal limits. There is tenderness on palpation over the bridge of her nose and between her eyes.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following anatomical structures is most likely involved in her symptoms?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Ethmoid sinus","Sphenoid sinus","Maxillary sinus","Frontal sinus","Nasal cavity"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe symptoms described, including facial pain and pressure around the eyes, are suggestive of sinusitis involving the \u003Cstrong\u003Eethmoid sinus\u003C/strong\u003E. The ethmoid sinus is located between the eyes and is part of the paranasal sinus system. It is composed of multiple small air cells within the ethmoid bone. Inflammation or infection of these sinuses can lead to the symptoms described.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Esphenoid sinus\u003C/strong\u003E is located deeper in the skull, behind the ethmoid sinuses, and when inflamed often presents as pain in the top of the head or the ear. \u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA \u003Cstrong\u003Emaxillary sinus\u003C/strong\u003E is located under each maxillary bone.  When inflamed they often causes pain in the cheeks or upper teeth.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Efrontal sinus\u003C/strong\u003E is located in the forehead, and inflammation typically causes pain in the forehead region.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Enasal cavity\u003C/strong\u003E is the space within the nose where air is inhaled and exhaled. Inflammation does not present as described here. \u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The ethmoid sinus is located between the eyes and is part of the paranasal sinus system.","The ethmoid sinus is composed of multiple small air cells and is situated within the ethmoid bone.","The ethmoid sinus produces mucous to lubricate the nasal passages."],"references":["Singh, V. (2023). Textbook of Anatomy-Head, Neck and Brain, Volume III-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Patel, C. R., Fernandez-Miranda, J. C., Wang, W. H., \u0026 Wang, E. W. (2016). Skull Base Anatomy. Otolaryngologic clinics of North America, 49(1), 9\u201320. https://doi.org/10.1016/j.otc.2015.09.001","Anderson, B. W., Kortz, M. W., Black, A. C., \u0026 Al Kharazi, K. A. (2023). Anatomy, Head and Neck, Skull. In StatPearls. StatPearls Publishing"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62009"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17961"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62009","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/62009"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-03T15:52:50+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-03T15:53:21+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10675"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76512"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"35","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/35"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc43","name":"Otorhinolaryngology","synonyms":["ENT","HEENT"],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-01-16T08:40:48+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"2"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"em